articles.title: Einstieg
articles.contents:
Einstieg_HL %>%
  ggplot(aes(Woche, Gramm)) +
   geom_line () +
  geom_point(colour= "#00868B", size = 4) +
    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 300)) +
    scale_x_continuous (limits = c(0,60), breaks= c(0, 1, 4, 25, 52, 60)) +
 #geom_smooth(method = "lm", colour= "grey") +
  labs(title = "Durchschnittliche Aufnahme von Plastik pro Person", subtitle = "Mikroplastik (in Gramm) pro Woche entspricht ungefähr...") +
   annotate(geom = "text", label= "Kreditkarte", x= 5.4, y= 2.5) + 
   annotate(geom= "text", label= "Zahnbürste", x= 9.2, y= 20) +
annotate(geom= "text", label= "Creme-Tube", x= 30, y= 120) +
   annotate(geom= "text", label= "Butter", x= 54.5,y= 250) +
    theme_test()

library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(cowplot)





global_plastic_fate <- readr::read_csv("data/global-plastic-fate.csv")

global_plastic_fate %>%
group_by(Entity) %>%
ggplot(aes(x = Year, y = `Estimated historic plastic fate`, color= Entity)) +
 geom_point()+
 scale_x_continuous(limits = c(1980, 2015), breaks = c(1980, 1990, 2000, 2010, 2015), expand = c(0.02,0.02))+
  labs(x= "", y= "prozentualer Anteil", title= "Globaler Kunststoffabfall differnziert nach Entsorgungsart, 1980 bis 2015")+
  scale_colour_discrete(name= "Entsorgungsart", breaks=c("Discarded", "Incinerated", "Recycled"),labels= c("Entsorgung (auf Mülldeponien)", "Verbrennung", "Recyceln"))+
  theme_minimal_hgrid(12)
